Definition.WordDefinition: Eighteen \Eight"een`\ ([=a]"t[=e]n`), a. [AS. eahtat[=y]ne, eahtat[=e]ne. See {Eight}, and {Ten}, and cf. {Eighty}.] Eight and ten; as, eighteen pounds. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition:
Eighteen \Eight"een`\, n. 1. The number greater by a unit than seventeen; eighteen units or objects. [1913 Webster]
2. A symbol denoting eighteen units, as 18 or xviii. [1913 Webster]
eighteen adj : being one more than seventeen [syn: {18}, {xviii}] n : the cardinal number that is the sum of seventeen and one [syn: {18}, {XVIII}]
